#
# Stand-in "login shell" for the lifecycle integration test
# (RemoteShellExitTriggersOnEnd). Like et-cat-shell, ET execs $SHELL as
# `execl($SHELL, $SHELL, "-l", NULL)` (PseudoUserTerminal.hpp, runTerminal),
# so this wrapper ignores its argv (the appended `-l`) entirely.
#
# It exits IMMEDIATELY (exit 0): the remote PTY child terminates, ET's
# UserTerminalHandler sees the shell die and tears the session down, and our
# client observes the terminal close -> on_end + ET_STATE_DISCONNECTED. Used
# to prove the remote-exit -> on_end lifecycle path (and, after it, et_close
# idempotency/null-safety).
exit 0
